00:31:56.839 --> 00:32:01.839
Not personally. It's more with our users.

00:32:01.839 --> 00:32:08.839
So the way we've tended to do it is they will own the –

00:32:08.839 --> 00:32:14.839
the team who are users of Posit would own the requirement and the risk and all of that.

00:32:14.839 --> 00:32:19.839
Unfortunately, this is something that Darren is probably better placed to talk about.

00:32:19.839 --> 00:32:24.839
Oh, Darren, I'm so sorry. We have a – we are missing you.

00:32:25.839 --> 00:32:37.839
But it – so we've got – we have a lot of existing processes around things like data protection

00:32:37.839 --> 00:32:44.839
and anti-bias and all of these kind of – they're all things you should be doing anyway,

00:32:44.839 --> 00:32:51.839
but it's a large organization and so they are very much formalized.

00:32:51.839 --> 00:32:57.839
Many of those things can be applied to the AI models.

00:32:57.839 --> 00:33:01.839
You need to be able to honestly answer the questions that people would have if they're going through

00:33:01.839 --> 00:33:11.839
something like a data protection assessment or a – because I imagine that your bosses,

00:33:11.839 --> 00:33:16.839
their worry is if I'm standing in court because of a discrimination case,

00:33:16.839 --> 00:33:23.839
because your AI has done something or a fraud thing, what do I say?

00:33:23.839 --> 00:33:32.839
Can you point me at something that says this was in a way that kind of would stand up?

00:33:32.839 --> 00:33:37.839
This was a reasonable thing to do. I think that's where the fear comes from,

00:33:37.839 --> 00:33:44.839
but it is methodically and carefully taking through – taking it through the steps.

00:33:45.839 --> 00:33:51.839
I suppose it's a similar thing to could we use a new cloud provider?

00:33:51.839 --> 00:33:57.839
Can I put companies' documentation in Dropbox?

00:33:57.839 --> 00:34:01.839
And you'd have to go through the steps to make that reasonable.

00:34:01.839 --> 00:34:05.839
It's been fairly similar to that sort of approach.

00:34:05.839 --> 00:34:07.839
It's similar and yet –

00:34:07.335 --> 00:34:17.655
It's similar and yet a little bit more scary for everybody because it's still this like

00:34:17.655 --> 00:34:24.134
unknown gray area. Megan had said in the chat our IT department handles all of the AI stuff.

00:34:24.134 --> 00:34:31.015
There's people dedicated to analyzing the risk and the deployment of that and we have a separate VPN

00:34:31.015 --> 00:34:36.214
that holds all the models and chatbots that we use. I think that that is a great interesting

